<TITLE> Bashundhara man arrested in Gazipur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, May 14 (bdnews24.com)  Gazipur police arrested a senior Bashundhara Group official early on Friday on charges of trespassing on government property, cutting earth and threatening government officers. Masum Hossain is a senior administrative officer of Bashundhara's Mouchak City Housing Project. Gazipur's Kaliakair police chief Mohammed Amir Hossain told bdnews24.com that Masum was arrested at the city's Madhyaparha. On Thursday, Mohammed Mokhlesur Rahman, assistant land officer of Shafipur union, filed two cases against Bashundhara Group chairman Ahmed Akbar Sobhan, popularly known as Shah Alam. The cases also charged another 40-50 unidentified people. The cases alleged that on Apr 28, 40-50 Bashundhara Group workers, on orders of their chairman, entered the government property at Madhyaparha Mouja and dug away earth for land-filling the housing project. Officials of the union's land office were threatened with 'dire consequences' when they had tried to stop the Bashundhara men, the cases stated. The next day, another 30-35 Bashundhara workers allegedly cut away earth from another government property in a similar manner. bdnews24.
